{
  "uuid": "4c8ce1e7738e1dcb5da1f39ca26f489e",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Receptionist cum Admin",
  "description": "<p><strong>Receptionist cum Admin (Feb 2026 - Dec 2027)</strong></p><p><strong>Duties:</strong></p><p>⦁ Manage front desk operations, handle telephone inquiries, and relay messages to appropriate personnel</p><p>⦁ Attend to sick / injured students</p><p>⦁ Contact parents of sick / injured students</p><p>⦁ Perform data entry work to support various school administrative functions</p><p>⦁ Assist to maintain accurate records of lost and found items, students resting in the sick bay, incidents and early release of students</p><p>⦁ Maintain stationeries/paper inventory</p><p>⦁ Housekeep the front desk area to ensure it remains orderly and professional</p><p>⦁ Issuance and recording of uniform on loan to students and ensure timely return in good order</p><p>⦁ Assist to keep the cupboards in the General Office clean and tidy, including those for the stationeries and uniform, to maintain an efficient working environment</p><p>⦁ Distribute mails to designated recipients in a timely manner.</p><p>⦁ Ensure items to be distributed are cleared and collected.</p><p>⦁ Inform teachers of their deliveries</p><p>⦁ Issue Report Books to students</p><p>⦁ Issue Graduation Certificates to graduated students.</p><p>⦁ Contact students for ad-hoc NRIC collection.</p><p>⦁ Help to pack items according to classes for distribution</p><p>⦁ Assist with lamination and binding of documents</p><p>⦁ Assist to update new staff name labeling at the pigeon holes</p><p>⦁ Perform other general administrative tasks as delegated by school management</p><p></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>⦁ At least 5 GCE O-Level passes</p><p>⦁ A minimum of 3 years of reception duties experience or equivalent</p><p>⦁ At least 3 years of experience using Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Word</p><p></p><p><strong>Working hours:</strong><br />Mon - Wed & Fri: 6.45am to 4.15pm (1hr lunch break)<br />Thursdays: 6.45am to 3.45pm (1hr lunch break)</p><p></p><p><strong>Location:</strong><br />Marine Parade</p><p>For interested candidates and for more information, please kindly send a WhatsApp message to 9630 3439!</p><p>EA License No. : 22C0937<br />EA Personnel No. : R23118390 (Gwen Lim)</p>",
